# ANSSI : Agence nationale de la sécurité des systèmes d'information
StrictHostKeyChecking: Prompt user for host key validation: ask
StrictModes: Verify file modes and permissions: yes
Ciphers: Supported encryption ciphers: aes256-ctr, aes192-ctr, aes128-ctr
MACs: Supported message authentication codes: hmac-sha2-512-etm, hmac-sha2-256-etm, hmac-sha1-etm
MACs: Supported message authentication codes for older versions: hmac-sha2-512, hmac-sha2-256, hmac-sha1
UsePrivilegeSeparation: Enable privilege separation with sandboxing: sandbox
Match group sftp-users: Match users in 'sftp-users' group for SFTP access
ForceCommand: Force use of internal-sftp for SFTP
ChrootDirectory: Set chroot directory to /sftp-home/%u
PermitEmptyPasswords: Allow empty passwords: no
MaxAuthTries: Maximum authentication attempts per connection: 2
LoginGraceTime: Timeframe for authentication (seconds): 30
PermitRootLogin: Allow remote access for root: no
PrintLastLog: Display last login details: yes
PermitUserEnvironment: Allow user environment modifications through sshd: no
AcceptEnv: List of user-alterable environment variables
ListenAddress: Listening address and port: A.B.C.D:26
AllowTcpForwarding: Enable or disable server-side forwarding: no
X11Forwarding: Enable or disable X11 forwarding: no
ForwardX11Trusted: Enable or disable trusted X11 forwarding: no
VerifyHostKeyDNS: Perform DNS fingerprint validation for ssh client: ask
